Custom fonts may not work on Android 5.0. See the following link for details:
https://code.google.com/p/android-developer-preview/issues/detail?id=608&thanks=608&ts=1404735239

This tool are used to verify and fix fonts for android developers.

OTS tool and TTX tool only works for Mac OS since these tools were built for MAC. Please build Windows version if you are working on Windows.
The re-encode script is written in Python and should work on all platforms.

********************************************
            Directory Overview
********************************************
----ot-sanitise
----ttx
----batch_reencode_script.py
----srcFonts
         FontFolder1
             font1
             font2
         FontFolder2
             font3
----dstFonts
         FontFolder1
             font1
             font2
         FontFolder2
             font3

********************************************
    Use ot-sanitise to valid fonts
********************************************
./ot-sanitise fontFile


********************************************
       Steps to Reencode the fonts
********************************************
1. Put all your font in the srcFonts folder
2. Run python batch_reencode_script.py
3. All the reencoded fonts are in dstFonts folder

